{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"adamantine-claimable-equine","description":"## Why\nThe grep-against-source inventory surfaced ANTI-PATTERN existence tests beyond the report's\nlist, each able to pass while the behavior is broken:\n`test_applier_exceptions.py` (three `hasattr`-only importability tests that never raise the\nerror); `test_applier_reschedule.py::test_exit_reschedule_constant_is_distinct` (`==75`);\n`test_fs_tools_extraction.py::test_fs_tools_exposes_the_shared_cluster` (7-symbol `hasattr`\nsweep); `test_overlap_retrieve.py::test_field_weights_constant` (exact private\n`_FIELD_WEIGHTS` values); `test_code_review_artifact.py::test_code_review_excluded_from_\njira_sync` (asserts `code_review` present/absent in reconciler source). VALIDATED.\n\n## What\nReplace each with a test that provokes the real behavior: trigger each exception path;\nassert EXIT_RESCHEDULE via the reschedule path that returns it; prove the fs_tools cluster\nvia the existing identity/reuse seam; exercise ranking that `_FIELD_WEIGHTS` drives; run\n`reconcile` and assert `code_review` tickets are excluded from Jira sync.\n\n## Scope\n- The five test files above.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Each error class is raised by exercising the failing path (not `hasattr`).\n- [ ] `EXIT_RESCHEDULE` and `_FIELD_WEIGHTS` are asserted via observable behavior, not\n      constant values.\n- [ ] `code_review` Jira exclusion is proven by running reconcile, not source grep.\n- [ ] fs_tools reuse is proven by identity, not existence.\n- [ ] `make test` green.","id":"003d-e6b0-9e58-4b52","parent_id":"bf50-2131-271b-4fdc","priority":3,"tags":["p2","change-detector","reconciler"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Replace hasattr/constant existence tests with behavioral provocation"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783784840020267001,"uuid":"07a0070a-b882-4aa8-a51d-4c7995e7fcde"}